⁣
1️⃣ Work hard, don’t give up. Keep at it every day. Results will come with your hard work.⁣
⁣
2️⃣ Give up the tasks you don’t HAVE to do. This is the toughest lesson I had to learn (the hard way of course). I loved bragging about being a 1 woman team but I’m even more proud to have a team of over 10 people to keep this ship running. Outsource your help so you can grow your business. ⁣
⁣
3️⃣ Networking. Being there for people in the industry when they need it, goes a longggg way. Pick and choose where you do the free work, it will help you in the long run. ⁣
⁣
4️⃣ Marketing. Decide where you want your business to go with your brand and stay on that route. Make sure your business is on brand with everything you do. Make sure your clients understand your brand. ⁣
⁣
5️⃣ Know your worth. Value how hard you’ve worked to create this business, people will realize the quality of your work is worth it. Once upon a time, I used to do all of this for practically free. I realized what I was worth as my business grew to now being a part of 225 weddings a year.⁣
⁣
6️⃣ Treat your clients like family - I absolutely adore getting to know my clients and I love being open and honest with them about what will and won’t work for their order. And of course the best part- being a part of their milestones for every event melts my heart. ❤️🫶⁣
⁣
